<Project Sdk="Dalamud.NET.Sdk/15.0.0">

  <PropertyGroup>
    <Author>LastOnionKnight</Author>
    <Name>Tonberry Tactics</Name>
    <InternalName>GearGoblin</InternalName>
    <AssemblyVersion>0.6.0</AssemblyVersion>
    <FileVersion>0.6.0</FileVersion>
    <Version>0.6.0</Version>
    <MinimumDalamudVersion>15.0.0</MinimumDalamudVersion>
    <Punchline>BiS planner, Materia Advisor, and round-trip optimizer for FFXIV. The in-game half of Tonberry Tactics; coexists with CharacterPanelRefined.</Punchline>
    <Description>The in-game half of Tonberry Tactics — BiS planner, gear inventory reader, materia advisor for FFXIV. Pairs with tonberrytactics.pages.dev over a copy-pasteable export/plan format. v0.6.0 ("Gear Division") ships the plugin's half of the v0.6.0 design port: IFontAtlas Phase 2 brings Cinzel (display serif), EB Garamond (body serif), and Press Start 2P (pixel) into the /tt window so plugin typography matches the web; the About tab gets the new wordmark lockup; the native CharacterStatus injection picks up TLF lantern-gold and frost accent colors on derived rows and the Materia Advisor section. Native injection still rides FFXIV's bundled SE font (the game's text node system can't accept plugin atlases); the typography refresh lands on the plugin's own ImGui surfaces. /tt, /ttexport, /ttimport, /ttinfo are the primary slash commands; /goblin* remain as deprecated aliases through v0.5.x. Coexists with CharacterPanelRefined (CPR derivations + GG advisor); full CPR-equivalent derivations are still here behind ForceDerivationsOverCpr or when CPR isn't installed. Materia formulas re-derived from public datamining sources.</Description>
    <RepoUrl>https://github.com/LastOnionKnight/GearGoblin</RepoUrl>
    <Tags>gear;bis;materia;etro;xivgear;raid;advisor;cpr;character-panel;tonberry-tactics</Tags>

    <Nullable>enable</Nullable>
    <LangVersion>latest</LangVersion>
    <AllowUnsafeBlocks>true</AllowUnsafeBlocks>
  </PropertyGroup>

  <!-- v0.4.7.1: brand artwork shipped alongside the DLL. Dalamud's SDK
       picks these up automatically via the Content glob and includes them
       in the plugin's install directory; runtime resolves via
       PluginInterface.AssemblyLocation.Directory + "Assets/" (see
       Services/BrandResources.cs). -->
  <ItemGroup>
    <Content Include="Assets\**\*.png">
      <CopyToOutputDirectory>PreserveNewest</CopyToOutputDirectory>
      <Pack>true</Pack>
    </Content>
  </ItemGroup>

  <!-- v0.6.0: custom .ttf fonts for IFontAtlas Phase 2. Same copy
       discipline as the brand artwork — runtime resolves the directory
       via PluginInterface.AssemblyLocation.Directory + "Assets/Fonts/"
       (see Theme/FontAtlasManager.cs). -->
  <ItemGroup>
    <Content Include="Assets\Fonts\*.ttf">
      <CopyToOutputDirectory>PreserveNewest</CopyToOutputDirectory>
      <Pack>true</Pack>
    </Content>
  </ItemGroup>

</Project>
